If removeAllTemp runs after each installation, it may break other parallel installations or lead to access violations. removeAllTemp really just removes the files inside the directory like it did before, how can it lead to any issues?
Commented on #390 feat: add customizable temp folder

removeAllTemp serves a fundamentally different purpose than the removal of a single temp folder. It is run on application startup and application shutdown to remove temporary directories that weren't removed normally after the application crashed or was killed or in case of any other malfunction of the application. If removeAllTemp runs after each installation, it may break other parallel installations or lead to access violations. Also the whole tempDir implementation using a single folder is fundamentally incompatible to parallel installations and might even lead to issues with a single installation at a time in case the folder wasn't removed properly before. So what is your suggestion? As requested, having a dedicated temporary folder that is customizable by the user is beneficial in regards to disk space.
